node.text:
@rosehoneyp & I made keto & diabetic friendly cauliflower hummus! 
RECIPE 👩🏻‍🍳 
1 medium size head cauliflower
4 cloves garlic
1/2 cup tahini
zest & juice of half lemon
1 tablespoon extra virgin olive oil
3/4 teaspoons salt
Few cracks of pepper

Bring a medium size pot of water to a boil and season with 1 tablespoon of salt. Meanwhile, cut the cauliflower florets into large bite size pieces and take the garlic out of the skin. Add to the boiling water and cook for 10 minutes. The cauliflower should be soft, but not mushy.

Drain well and add to a blender with the tahini, lemon zest & juice, olive oil, salt, and pepper. Blend on high for 1 minute, adding a touch more water if the consistency is too thick. Check for seasoning and enjoy!

@rosehoneyp & I made keto & diabetic friendly cauliflower hummus! 
RECIPE 👩🏻‍🍳 
1 medium size head cauliflower
4 cloves garlic
1/2 cup tahini
zest & juice of half lemon
1 tablespoon extra virgin olive oil
3/4 teaspoons salt
Few cracks of pepper

Bring a medium size pot of water to a boil and season with 1 tablespoon of salt. Meanwhile, cut the cauliflower florets into large bite size pieces and take the garlic out of the skin. Add to the boiling water and cook for 10 minutes. The cauliflower should be soft, but not mushy.

Drain well and add to a blender with the tahini, lemon zest & juice, olive oil, salt, and pepper. Blend on high for 1 minute, adding a touch more water if the consistency is too thick. Check for seasoning and enjoy!

node.text:
Breakfast Burritos w/ @rosehoneyp 🌯 RECIPE: 
4 eggs
1 cup frozen cauliflower rice
1 cup cheddar cheese
3 sausage links
2 burrito wraps(i used siete brand)
Sour cream( i used forager brand)
Salsa( i used frontera double roasted)

First prepare all the ingredients:
Cook the frozen cauliflower rice in a pan with salt and pepper until warmed through, about 7 minutes. Whisk the ggs season with salt and pepper, and scramble them in a pan. Grate the cheddar cheese and cook the sausage then chop it up. 

Make the burrito:
Warm the burrito wrap in a large pan until soft and pliable, about 30 seconds per side. Add some cauliflower rice towards the edge and top with eggs, chopped sausage, some cheese, and sour cream. Fold the burrito and then make the second one. 

Preheat a pan over medium heat with 2 teaspoons of oil and a pinch of salt. Place both burritos seam side down and cook until golden brown, about 3 minutes. Flip and cook another 2-3 minutes. Remove and put a layer of grated cheese in the pan, the same size as the burrito, and then put the burritos back in. Allow to cook until the edges get golden brown, about 3 minutes. Use a spatula to carefully remove the burritos and put them on a plate cheese side. Let cool for a few minutes then enjoy!
